# Cloudflare Pages — HTTP response headers
# Format docs: https://developers.cloudflare.com/pages/configuration/headers/
# This file MUST live in the build output directory root (same folder as index.html).
#
# The Content-Security-Policy below is the Path A + Layer 1 baseline for SakhaPR.
# It is intentionally strict. If you add an optional phase, widen ONLY the one
# directive named in the comment, and document the origin in PRIVACY.md / DPIA.md.

/*
  Content-Security-Policy: default-src 'self'; script-src 'self' 'wasm-unsafe-eval'; worker-src 'self' blob:; style-src 'self'; font-src 'self'; img-src 'self' blob: data:; connect-src 'self'; form-action 'self' mailto:; base-uri 'self'; object-src 'none'; frame-ancestors 'none'
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  Referrer-Policy: no-referrer
  Permissions-Policy: geolocation=(), microphone=(), camera=()
  X-Frame-Options: DENY

# Why each non-obvious directive is here:
#   script-src 'wasm-unsafe-eval' .. Tesseract.js (Phase 5) compiles WASM in-browser.
#   worker-src 'self' blob: ......... Tesseract.js spawns a Web Worker (locally vendored).
#   img-src blob: data: ............. eKTP preview via object URL + canvas downscale.
#   form-action 'self' mailto: ...... Phase 6 Path A opens a prefilled mailto: draft.
#
# Phase 7 (optional, semantic search): add the Transformers.js model origin to
#   connect-src AND script-src — name the exact origin, then refresh the DPIA.
# Phase 8 (optional, Path B relay): add ONLY your relay origin to connect-src.
